flowers.name: Evergreen oak
flowers.description: A member of the white oak group, the canyon live oak (Q. chrysolepis) is a timber tree that occasionally grows more than 27 metres (89 feet) tall. It is often called goldencup oak for its egg-shaped acorns, each enclosed at the base in a yellow woolly cup.

flowers.name: Rose (Rosa)
flowers.description: Roses are popular and beautiful flowering plants known for their fragrant blooms.

flowers.name: Sunflower (Helianthus annuus)
flowers.description: Sunflowers are large, bright yellow flowers that resemble the sun. They are known for their tall stems and large, round blooms.

flowers.name: Tulip (Tulipa)
flowers.description: Tulips are beautiful, cup-shaped flowers that come in a wide range of colors. They are often associated with spring.

flowers.name: Orchid (Orchidaceae)
flowers.description: Orchids are exotic and elegant flowers known for their vibrant colors and unique shapes. They are highly prized and symbolize beauty and luxury.

flowers.name: Lily (Lilium)
flowers.description: Lilies are fragrant flowers with large, showy blooms. They come in various colors and are often used in floral arrangements.

flowers.name: Daffodil (Narcissus)
flowers.description: Daffodils are cheerful, yellow flowers with a trumpet-shaped center. They are often one of the first flowers to bloom in spring.

flowers.name: Iris (Iris)
flowers.description: Irises are elegant flowers known for their vibrant colors and unique shape. They are often used in bouquets and garden beds.

flowers.name: Carnation (Dianthus caryophyllus)
flowers.description: Carnations are popular flowers with ruffled petals and a spicy fragrance. They are available in a wide range of colors.

flowers.name: Pansy (Viola tricolor)
flowers.description: Pansies are delicate flowers with velvety petals and distinctive markings. They are available in a wide array of colors.

flowers.name: Geranium (Pelargonium)
flowers.description: Geraniums are versatile flowering plants with vibrant blooms and aromatic foliage. They are often used in containers and garden beds.

flowers.name: Daisy (Bellis perennis)
flowers.description: Daisies are charming flowers with white petals and a yellow center. They are often associated with innocence and purity.

flowers.name: Lavender (Lavandula)
flowers.description: Lavender is a fragrant herb with beautiful purple flowers. It is often used for its soothing aroma and as a decorative plant.

flowers.name: Marigold (Tagetes)
flowers.description: Marigolds are vibrant flowers known for their bold colors and strong scent. They are often used in gardens as companion plants.

flowers.name: Poppy (Papaver)
flowers.description: Poppies are delicate flowers with vibrant petals that come in various colors. They are often associated with remembrance.

flowers.name: Jasmine (Jasminum)
flowers.description: Jasmine is a fragrant flowering plant with small, star-shaped white flowers. It is treasured for its sweet and intoxicating scent.

flowers.name: Hibiscus (Hibiscus)
flowers.description: Hibiscus is a tropical flower with large, showy blooms in a variety of colors. It is often associated with beauty and femininity.

flowers.name: Hydrangea (Hydrangea)
flowers.description: Hydrangeas are large, colorful flowers that bloom in clusters. They are known for their ability to change color based on the acidity of the soil.

flowers.name: Peony (Paeonia)
flowers.description: Peonies are large, fragrant flowers with soft petals that come in various colors. They are often used in bridal bouquets and symbolize romance and prosperity.

flowers.name: Snapdragon (Antirrhinum)
flowers.description: Snapdragons are tall, colorful flowers with unique, dragon-like blooms. They are popular in floral arrangements and add vertical interest to gardens.

flowers.name: Petunia (Petunia)
flowers.description: Petunias are small, trumpet-shaped flowers that come in a wide range of colors. They are versatile plants that can be used in containers, hanging baskets, or flower beds.

flowers.name: Zinnia (Zinnia)
flowers.description: Zinnias are bright and colorful flowers that bloom abundantly. They are easy to grow and attract butterflies, making them a popular choice for gardens.

flowers.name: Chrysanthemum (Chrysanthemum)
flowers.description: Chrysanthemums, or mums, are popular fall flowers known for their vibrant colors and variety of bloom shapes. They symbolize optimism and joy.

flowers.name: Azalea (Rhododendron)
flowers.description: Azaleas are flowering shrubs with clusters of vibrant, trumpet-shaped blooms. They are often used in landscaping and add a pop of color to gardens.

flowers.name: Freesia (Freesia)
flowers.description: Freesias are delicate, fragrant flowers that come in a range of colors. They are often used in floral arrangements and symbolize friendship and innocence.

flowers.name: Cosmos (Cosmos bipinnatus)
flowers.description: Cosmos are daisy-like flowers with delicate, feathery foliage. They come in various colors and are loved for their ability to attract butterflies and bees.

flowers.name: Crocus (Crocus)
flowers.description: Crocus flowers are small, cup-shaped blooms that are among the first to appear in spring. They come in various colors and are known for their resilience.

flowers.name: Gerbera Daisy (Gerbera)
flowers.description: Gerbera daisies are cheerful flowers known for their large, colorful blooms. They are popular in floral arrangements and symbolize happiness and purity.

flowers.name: Foxglove (Digitalis purpurea)
flowers.description: Foxglove is a tall, showy flower with bell-shaped blooms that attract bees and hummingbirds. It comes in various colors and is often found in cottage gardens.

flowers.name: Morning Glory (Ipomoea)
flowers.description: Morning glory is a climbing vine with vibrant, trumpet-shaped flowers that open in the morning and close in the afternoon. It symbolizes love and affection.

flowers.name: Hollyhock (Alcea rosea)
flowers.description: Hollyhocks are tall, majestic flowers with large, showy blooms that come in various colors. They are often used in cottage gardens and add vertical interest.

flowers.name: Anemone (Anemone)
flowers.description: Anemones are delicate, daisy-like flowers with colorful petals. They are often used in floral arrangements and symbolize anticipation and protection against evil.

flowers.name: Gladiolus (Gladiolus)
flowers.description: Gladiolus is a tall, elegant flower with sword-shaped leaves and vibrant, funnel-shaped blooms. It is often used in floral arrangements and symbolizes strength and integrity.

flowers.name: Peacock Flower (Caesalpinia pulcherrima)
flowers.description: The peacock flower is a tropical shrub known for its striking, bird-like flowers in vibrant colors. It attracts butterflies and adds a touch of exotic beauty to gardens.

flowers.name: Bird of Paradise (Strelitzia reginae)
flowers.description: Bird of Paradise is a tropical plant with unique, bird-like flowers that resemble the plumage of a tropical bird. It symbolizes freedom and paradise.

flowers.name: Bleeding Heart (Dicentra)
flowers.description: Bleeding Heart is a delicate, heart-shaped flower with drooping blooms that resemble bleeding hearts. It is often used in shaded gardens and symbolizes love and compassion.

flowers.name: Columbine (Aquilegia)
flowers.description: Columbine is a charming, bell-shaped flower with spurred petals that attract hummingbirds. It comes in various colors and is often found in cottage gardens.

flowers.name: Black-eyed Susan (Rudbeckia hirta)
flowers.description: Black-eyed Susan is a bright, daisy-like flower with a dark center and golden-yellow petals. It is native to North America and attracts butterflies and bees.

flowers.name: Canterbury Bells (Campanula medium)
flowers.description: Canterbury Bells is a bell-shaped flower that comes in various colors, including purple, pink, and white. It adds a touch of charm to cottage gardens and flower beds.

flowers.name: Delphinium (Delphinium)
flowers.description: Delphinium is a tall, majestic flower with vibrant, spiky blooms in shades of blue, purple, pink, and white. It adds vertical interest to gardens and bouquets.

flowers.name: Sweet Pea (Lathyrus odoratus)
flowers.description: Sweet Pea is a fragrant, climbing flower with colorful, ruffled blooms in shades of pink, purple, and white. It is often used in bouquets and symbolizes blissful pleasure.

flowers.name: Wisteria (Wisteria)
flowers.description: Wisteria is a woody, climbing vine known for its cascading clusters of fragrant, pea-like flowers in shades of purple, pink, and white. It adds a romantic touch to gardens.

flowers.name: Magnolia (Magnolia)
flowers.description: Magnolia is a flowering tree with large, showy blooms in shades of white, pink, and purple. It is known for its fragrant flowers and adds elegance to any landscape.

flowers.name: Buttercup (Ranunculus)
flowers.description: Buttercup is a small, bright yellow flower with glossy petals. It is native to meadows and grasslands and adds a cheerful touch to gardens and floral arrangements.

flowers.name: Iceland Poppy (Papaver nudicaule)
flowers.description: Iceland Poppy is a delicate flower with papery, cup-shaped blooms in shades of orange, yellow, pink, and white. It adds a touch of whimsy to gardens and flower beds.

flowers.name: Monkshood (Aconitum)
flowers.description: Monkshood is a tall, spiky flower with helmet-shaped blooms in shades of blue, purple, and white. It is a stunning addition to shady gardens and attracts hummingbirds.

flowers.name: Snowdrop (Galanthus)
flowers.description: Snowdrop is a delicate, bell-shaped flower that blooms in late winter or early spring. It is one of the first flowers to appear, signaling the arrival of spring.

flowers.name: Cornflower (Centaurea cyanus)
flowers.description: Cornflower is a charming wildflower with vibrant blue blooms. It attracts bees and butterflies and is often used in cottage gardens and meadow-inspired landscapes.

flowers.name: Violet (Viola odorata)
flowers.description: Violet is a small, fragrant flower with purple, blue, or white petals. It thrives in shaded areas and is often used as ground cover or in woodland gardens.
